{
  "type": "contentBlock",
  "flexDirection": "column",
  "id": "pipeline_hero",
  "ariaLabel": "Pipeline intro",
  "width": ["100%", "92%"],
  "height": "hug",
  "align": ["full", "center"],
  "fill": "oklch(from var(--pb-secondary) l c h / 0.5)",
  "borderRadius": ["2rem 2rem 0 0", "4rem 4rem 0 0"],
  "elementOrder": ["hero-heading", "hero-subtitle", "hero-body"],
  "effects": [
    {
      "type": "backdropBlur",
      "amount": "24px"
    }
  ],
  "definitions": {
    "hero-heading": {
      "type": "elementHeading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Make it all data",
      "align": "center",
      "width": "hug",
      "wordWrap": true,
      "marginTop": "2rem",
      "marginBottom": "0.5rem",
      "motionTiming": {
        "entrancePreset": "fade",
        "entranceMotion": {
          "transition": {
            "delay": 0.1
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "hero-subtitle": {
      "type": "elementHeading",
      "level": 4,
      "text": "Why I built a page builder as a pipeline",
      "align": "center",
      "width": "hug",
      "wordWrap": true,
      "marginBottom": ["1.5rem", "2rem"],
      "motionTiming": {
        "entrancePreset": "slideUp",
        "entranceMotion": {
          "transition": {
            "delay": 0.2
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "hero-body": {
      "type": "elementBody",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "I tried building a site in Node. Routes, components, copy—everything was code. Adding a page meant new files and new routes. I wanted something easier and reusable. So the idea became: treat the site as data. One pipeline. Load → Expand → Resolve → Render. This is how that pipeline works, and why it’s shaped this way.",
      "align": "center",
      "textAlign": "center",
      "width": ["90%", "66%"],
      "wordWrap": true,
      "marginBottom": ["2rem", "3rem"],
      "motionTiming": {
        "entrancePreset": "slideUp",
        "entranceMotion": {
          "transition": {
            "delay": 0.35
          }
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "gap": "1rem"
}
